                                                            "IfChoice", "2", "TreasureGet", "Locked603",
                                                            "SetChoice", "2", "TreasureGet",
                                                            "When you try to open the door, you find that it clicks open without resistance, letting you swing it open to reveal-",
                                                            "A small apartment room painted in stark whites and crisp blues, vacant of normal furniture, but adorned with prop rocks dotted about the place while little snowflake cutouts hang from the ceiling on little strings, giving the area an unexpected wintry atmosphere... In fact, there's even a slightly chilly breeze flowing through the premises, blowing from an unknown origin...",
                                                            "DisplayCharacters",
                                                              "2",
                                                            "EndLoop",
                                                            "However, the most eye-catching and prominent feature of the chamber is undoubtedly the wooden treasure chest proudly sitting in the center of the faux snowy landscape, adorned with a plaque etched onto its front that you're only able to read after stepping deeper into the room, driven by curiosity.",
                                                            "Scanning the note cursively etched onto the box, you see that it reads: {i}'You found the secret Dragon Treasure of Harpy Mountain! Congratulations! Enjoy your reward, and always stay inquisitive. - E.R.'{/i}",
                                                            "Increasingly feeling like this isn't some kind of multi-layered trap to sucker you in, but actually just a genuine nice surprise, you flip open the chest's lid and discover a number of what looks to be packs of 'Dragon Bubble Puzzle Gum', the name being written in big conspicuous letters on the colorful packaging.",
                                                            "GiveItem", "5", "Dragon Bubble Puzzle Gum",
                                                            "... And along with the strange candy, you also plunder a single, red reptilian scale, the item seeming to glow with a faint light and heat of its own, instilling you with a feeling of self-assurance as you grip it in your hand. Incidentally, you also notice that it seems to be just the right size to fit where you usually slot in your active runes in your Grimoire...",
                                                            "GiveItem", "1", "Dragon Scale Rune",
                                                            "DisplayCharacters",
                                                            "EndLoop",
                                                            "Stowing away the profitable if a bit strange windfall, you take a moment to survey the chilled room in order to make sure that you didn't miss anything, then with your inquisitiveness (and greed) sated, you leave the place, closing the door behind you while appreciating the warm glint of your rune-engraved prize as you pocket it among the rest of your belongings.",
